This paper focuses on program comprehension, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of semantic clustering and topic analysis, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (cs.PL, cs.LG). The paper also introduces context models for source code identifiers, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) applied to source code (cs.IR, cs.CL).
